OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FMichael Grade has said under-16s
OL,7,Fshould be banned from accessing social
OL,8,Fmedia, arguing that the harms to
OL,9,Fchildren are now so serious that
OL,10,F"dramatic action" is justified.
OL,12,FThe former chair of Ofcom, who has
OL,13,Falso run the BBC, ITV and Channel 4,
OL,14,Fsays his view is personal rather than
OL,15,Fregulatory policy.
OL,17,FBut after years overseeing the
OL,18,Fimplementation of the Online Safety
OL,19,FAct, he believes there is "nothing to
OL,20,Flose" from introducing a time-limited
OL,21,Fban, reviewed regularly by Parliament.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@QO]{D@[OU|D@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/20
