FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FAll of the major tech companies insist
OL,7,Fthey take the protection of children
OL,8,Fseriously and are committing energy
OL,9,Fand resources to reducing harmful
OL,10,Fcontent on their platforms.
OL,12,FAt the same time, Grade strongly
OL,13,Fdefends Ofcom's record, despite
OL,14,Fcriticism that the regulator has yet
OL,15,Fto fine a single major social media
OL,16,Fplatform under the Online Safety Act,
OL,17,Fwhich became law in 2023.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FLast week, a report by Ofcom found
OL,7,Fthat 73% of children aged 11 to 17 are
OL,8,Fstill exposed to harmful content
OL,9,Fonline.
OL,11,FOfcom said that while Meta, Snap and
OL,12,FRoblox had agreed to make changes,
OL,13,FTikTok and YouTube had failed to set
OL,14,Fout meaningful steps to protect
OL,15,Fchildren and judged their feeds "still
OL,16,Fnot safe enough".
OL,18,FCritics argue that more than two years
OL,19,Fafter the Act was introduced,
OL,20,Finvestigations and warnings are no
OL,21,Fsubstitute for enforcement.
OL,26,@wD@aOUxD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FCaroline Dinenage MP, chair of the
OL,7,FCulture, Media and Sport Committee,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Ofcom has the teeth, but they
OL,9,Fdon't appear to have the stomach. They
OL,10,Fare too cautious."
OL,12,FGrade rejects that criticism. "Ofcom
OL,13,Fis not a star chamber," he said.
OL,15,FRegulators, he argues, cannot simply
OL,16,Fissue huge fines because of headlines
OL,17,For political pressure.
OL,19,FThe Online Safety Act requires
OL,20,Fconsultation, evidence gathering and
OL,21,Fdue process.
OL,26,@pD@GOUrD@RO]tD@_OUuD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FEvery major decision has to be capable
OL,7,Fof surviving judicial review against
OL,8,Fsome of the richest companies in the
OL,9,Fworld.
OL,11,FHe insists fines against major
OL,12,Fplatforms are coming, but says the
OL,13,Fprocess is necessarily painstaking
OL,14,Fbecause tech companies challenge every
OL,15,Fstage.
OL,17,F"You've got to compile the evidence,"
OL,18,Fhe said. "You can't just fine them on
OL,19,Fthe basis of anecdotal stuff."
OL,26,@yD@AOUyD@eO]zD@JOU{D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FBeyond tech regulation, Grade paints a
OL,7,Fstark picture of the pressures facing
OL,8,FBritain's traditional broadcasters.
OL,10,FITV, Channel 4 and Channel 5 face what
OL,11,Fhe calls an "existential" challenge as
OL,12,Faudiences and advertising move online.
OL,14,FWhile he says the BBC's licence fee
OL,15,Fgives it a degree of protection,
OL,16,Fcommercial broadcasters are being
OL,17,Fsqueezed by YouTube and US streaming
OL,18,Fplatforms like Netflix.
OL,20,F'It needs to come down': Grade says
OL,21,Fthe BBC licence fee is too expensive
OL,26,@sD@MOUsD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FFor Grade, the roots of the crisis go
OL,7,Fback nearly two decades - to the
OL,8,Fcollapse of Project Kangaroo.
OL,10,FProject Kangaroo was the joint
OL,11,Fstreaming platform proposed by the
OL,12,FBBC, ITV and Channel 4 in the late
OL,13,F2000s, years before Netflix became
OL,14,Fdominant in Britain. Competition
OL,15,Fregulators blocked it in 2009, arguing
OL,16,Fit could reduce competition in online
OL,17,Ftelevision.
OL,19,FGrade believes that the decision was
OL,20,Fcalamitous.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,F"We just handed the market to the
OL,7,FAmericans," he said. "It was the most
OL,8,Fdisgraceful, idiotic, short-sighted
OL,9,Fand ignorant regulatory decision.
OL,10,FWe're paying the price for that now."
OL,12,FHe argues that Britain might now have
OL,13,Fhad a streaming platform of real
OL,14,Fscale, carrying British public-service
OL,15,Fcontent, rather than relying on
OL,16,FAmerican technology giants.
OL,18,FThat view shapes his thinking on the
OL,19,Ffuture of ITV and Sky.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@KO]oD@VOUrD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FHe said consolidation in commercial
OL,7,Fbroadcasting is increasingly
OL,8,Finevitable and says he has no
OL,9,Fobjection in principle to Sky buying
OL,10,FITV's broadcast business if the deal
OL,11,Fproceeds.
OL,13,F"Scale is very, very important," he
OL,14,Fsaid.
OL,16,FSky is owned by the American media
OL,17,Fgiant Comcast.
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FGrade believes the key issue for
OL,7,Fregulators would not be ownership
OL,8,Fitself, but the future of impartial
OL,9,Ftelevision news.
OL,11,FComcast's takeover of Sky in 2018 was
OL,12,Fapproved only after the company
OL,13,Fguaranteed funding for Sky News for
OL,14,Ften years - that guarantee expires
OL,15,Fsoon.
OL,17,F"There's no reason why Comcast needs
OL,18,Fto do Sky News if they don't want to,"
OL,19,Fhe said, suggesting the future of Sky
OL,20,FNews and ITN would become central to
OL,21,Fany public interest test.
OL,26,@yD@AOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
