CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FOn the BBC, Grade remains a defender
OL,7,Fof the licence fee, though not at its
OL,8,Fcurrent level.
OL,10,F"I don't know a better way," he said,
OL,11,Frejecting subscription as a model that
OL,12,Fwould fundamentally change the BBC's
OL,13,Foutput by forcing it to chase mass-
OL,14,Fmarket hits rather than distinctive
OL,15,Fpublic-service programming.
OL,17,FBut he also argues the licence fee,
OL,18,Fwhich currently costs #180 a year,
OL,19,Fshould be cut.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,F"We need the licence fee to come
OL,7,Fdown," Grade said, who was chair of
OL,8,Fthe BBC between 2004 and 2006.
OL,10,F"We get stories every night, quite
OL,11,Frightly, on (BBC) TV and on the radio
OL,12,Fabout the cost of living crisis;
OL,13,Fmeanwhile, in another part of the BBC,
OL,14,Fthey're asking for more money."
OL,16,FThe BBC is already in the process of
OL,17,Fbelt-tightening. As many as 2,000 jobs
OL,18,Fare set to be lost as part of a #600
OL,19,Fmillion cost-cutting plan, many of
OL,20,Fthem in the news.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@FO]rD@AOUsD@MpmsD@QpnvD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FBut Grade rejects the idea that
OL,7,Ffurther savings would weaken the
OL,8,Forganisation.
OL,10,F"They've got buildings all over the
OL,11,FUK... they've got palaces outside
OL,12,FLondon which they don't need.
OL,13,FEveryone's working from home today,"
OL,14,Fhe said. "There's a lot of cost to
OL,15,Fcome out of the BBC."
OL,17,FThe broadcaster he worries about most,
OL,18,Fhowever, is Channel 4. He describes it
OL,19,Fas "the corner shop in a world of
OL,20,Fsupermarkets", lacking the scale of
OL,21,Fthe BBC, Sky or the US streamers.
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@dO]vD@JOUwD@UO]{D@DOU|D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31217
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779966178
OL,3,C'Wild west for tech firms': Ex-Ofcom
OL,4,Cboss backs under-16s social media ban
OL,6,FCan it survive? "The jury's out," he
OL,7,Fsaid. "I hope that it will."
OL,9,FGrade also strongly defends GB News,
OL,10,Frejecting criticism that it operates
OL,11,Fto a lower standard of impartiality
OL,12,Fand truth than other broadcasters.
OL,14,FNigel Farage is one of GB News' star
OL,15,Fpresenters. Grade says he does not
OL,16,Fhave a problem with elected
OL,17,Fpoliticians or leaders of political
OL,18,Fparties presenting programmes on a
OL,19,Fnews channel.
OL,26,@nD@QOUnD@aO]oD@GOUoD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
